# shellcheck configuration for notenav
#
# Project convention: bare $var (not ${var}), so disable brace-style checks.
# AWK bodies live in single-quoted strings, so $-in-single-quotes is expected.
# lib/notenav.sh is sourced by bin/nn, so cross-file variable refs are normal.

# SC2250 (style)  – prefer ${var} braces; project uses bare $var consistently
# SC2312 (info)   – mask return value in $(); handled correctly throughout
# SC2016 (info)   – $ in single quotes; all AWK/jq strings, intentional
# SC2153 (info)   – possible misspelling; false positive for sourced NOTENAV_ROOT
# SC2310 (info)   – function in if/! disables set -e; intentional in installer
disable=SC2250,SC2312,SC2016,SC2153,SC2310
